<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1919-01-18T12:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1919-01-18T12:00:00-05:00" n="13" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d13">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">861.00/3664: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Commission to Negotiate
                                    Peace</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Paris</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-01-18T17:00:00+00:00"><hi rend="italic">January 18,
                                        1919, 5 p.m.</hi></date><lb/>[Received 6:34
                            p.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>330. Your 200, January 12, 8 p.m. Replying to your confidential inquiry
                            contained in last sentence, can only say that explanation of publicity
                            here is to be found in internal political situation.</p>
                        <closer><signed><persName corresp="#p_LR1"><hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi></persName></signed>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Am</hi>[<hi rend="smallcaps">erican</hi>] <hi rend="smallcaps">Mission</hi></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>